extends ../../../module_layout

block content

  .ui.container#raised-container.top-padding
    .limit
      h1.ui.header.large#learn-title
        .content
          | How can you protect yourself before being contacted by scammers?
      .dosContainer
        .ui.large.blue.fluid.label
          i.thumbs.up.icon 
          | Do's

      .ui.bulleted.list 
        .item Always take new online relationships slowly.
        .item Talk with your friends and family about any new relationships for an non-biased perspective.
        .item Be cautious of profiles with very minimal pictures of themselves and others.
        .item Update your privacy settings on social media so that only trusted loves ones can see what you share.
        .item 
          b Carefully examine phone numbers, website addresses, and email addresses for inconsistencies. 
      img.ui.centered.fluid.image(src='/images/romance-submod3learn3.jpg' alt="example text messages from lucy")
      .ui.icon.blue.message
        .icon
          img#dart_image1.ui.small.image.right.floated(src='/profile_pictures/transparent.png')
        .content
          .header
            | Important
          p These texts are a clear example of the type of inconsistencies Romance and Friendship scammers may have. Lucy originally says she has always lived in the United States, but then texts from an international number. This is a strong sign that Lucy is not who she says she is! 
    
    
    script.
        var progress = #{user.moduleProgress.identity.percent}
    script(src='/js/setProgressBar.js')  

block append footer
  .ui.container
    +navButtons('romance', 'sub3_learn3', '/learn/submod3/2/romance', '/learn/submod3/4/romance', 84, 'Back', 'Next')  

